üîß What is Engineering?

Engineering is the application of science and mathematics to design, build, and improve machines, structures, systems, and processes.
Engineers solve real-world problems using technical knowledge and practical skills.
It helps in developing technology that improves human life and society.

üèóÔ∏è Main Branches of Engineering

Mechanical Engineering
Deals with machines, engines, manufacturing, and thermal systems.

Civil Engineering
Focuses on construction of buildings, bridges, roads, and dams.

Electrical Engineering
Concerned with electricity, power generation, and electrical systems.

Electronics & Communication Engineering
Works with electronic devices, circuits, and communication systems.

Computer Engineering
Involves software, hardware, and programming.

